We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
instruct the City Engineer to facilitate the immediate submission of reports on issued building permits and copy of all supporting documents to the Assessor’s Office to expedite the preparation and issuance of the corresponding Real Property Tax Declaration to the respective property owners;
require the City Assessor to closely coordinate with the Office of the City Engineer on matters affecting the preparation of updated reports on real property taxes;
review and evaluate the number and qualifications of personnel assigned in the City Assessor’s Office and make the necessary adjustments, if any, in order to improve the performance of that Office; and
provide assistance to the Office of the City Assessor on their need for service vehicle in the scheduled inspection and validation. This will enable that unit to cover, if possible, the whole area of jurisdiction of the City and in order to maximize the time allotted by that unit for such undertakings.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
direct the LGU officials concerned to strictly monitor the implementation of their respective projects as planned and within the prescribed time frame and take note of any gap for future inputs;
instruct the BuB Focal Person to coordinate with their counterpart officials from national government agencies and make follow ups in order to ascertain the reasons for non-receipt of funds from the source NGAs. This will enable the LGU to plan the next steps to be taken in case the original project is no longer viable and responsive to the needs of the intended beneficiaries;
direct the respective Heads of the Offices concerned to submit to the  Office of the Auditor a copy of Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) executed by and between the LGU and the partner NGAs in compliance with Section 6.5 of COA Circular 94-013; and
remind the Head of the City Planning and Development Office, City Engineering Office (MEO) and other LGU officials concerned to prepare in advance and make available all necessary documents that would substantiate the requirements of the funding agencies in order to comply with the 60 days allowable period of submission of the same to the source agencies.
